3 Low-Level Interface
*********************

The low-level interface is a straight wrapper of the C entry points
provided by the Reduce library, also known as the "procedural" or
PROC(1) interface, for short.  It uses an embedded version of Reduce
which runs on a free and open-source Lisp flavour known as CSL(2)
(Codemist Standard Lisp).  The external C routines are all declared in
the ‘reduce’ namespace.  Normally you shouldn’t have to call these
functions directly, since we provide a high-level, idiomatic Pure
interface which makes calling Reduce from Pure much easier, see below.

