6.6 Even and Odd Operators
==========================

An operator can be declared to be even or odd in its first argument by
the declarations ‘EVEN’ and ‘ODD’ respectively.

     > declare operator [f1,f2];
     []
     > declare odd f1;
     []
     > declare even f2;
     []

     > simplify $ f1(-a);
     -f1 a

     > simplify $ f2 (-a);
     f2 a

     > simplify $ f1 (-a) (-b);
     -f1 a (-b)



