6.11 Internal Order of Variables
================================

It is possible for the user to change the internal order of variables by
means of the declaration ‘KORDER’.  The syntax for this is:

 -- Describe: declare korder [v1,...,vn]

  Unlike the ORDER declaration, which has a purely cosmetic effect on
the way results are printed, the use of KORDER can have a significant
effect on computation time.

     > declare korder [z,y,x];
     []
     > x+y+z;
     x+y+z
     > simplify $ x+y+z;
     z+y+x



